reviews.text: Is that like a place where they keep birds what is the Avery building never been there
Just a great experience be going back again
I had no idea this restoration project was here.  The very narrow bathroom doors stick out as the most significant
Interesting

Where to begin...well first and foremost, Black Bottle makes some amazing and often unique beers. I recently had Scuba Sam, which is a bigger version of Scuba Steve...weighing in at 10.2%. While that is admittedly high, you would never guess it was 10.2 because it was ridiculously easy to drink; tread lightly if you choose Scuba Sam. Secondly...the food. WOW! I mean, seriously, they have a really unique and varied menu with truly something for everyone. I had the sliders and I simply could not get enough. (But one does need to stop at some point...😆.) To top it off, they do have a full bar; so if beer is not your thing, you'll definitely find something. And they don't just have their own beers; they have other craft beer as well. Oh and the patio...very nice when the weather is cooperative. Just go. You won't regret it. Cheers!

Been going here for quite a while. Fantastic beer selection both their own and plenty of other "guest" beer choices. The menu gives a little information on the taste, IBU's, etc. so you have an idea of what you are getting. The food is also good! A beer lovers heaven!!

One of my top places in Fort Collins! They have GREAT beer (their holiday beers are always fantastic)! If you haven't tried their oyster shots, it's an experience you have to do! Great food if you want to have a meal or just snack. Beth is the best bartender. She always has great recommendations! Make this one of your go to places in FoCo!

Enjoyable beer. Had the Scuba Steve, Friar Chuck, and Oatmeal Stout. Meatball sandwich was AMAZING. It might have been that I was hungry, but I thoroughly enjoyed that sandwich. Place had a cool vibe. Only reason it got 4 stars was the flat bread left something to be desired. It was underwhelming, the crust could use some improvement and there wasn't enough sauce. 

Overall we would go again, but will be skipping the flat bread.

Not my best brewpub experience.  Went with the wife & 2 kids (5yr & 9mo) on a Monday night.  Curious staff and prompt service.  No issues there.

I had their brown ale & found it didbt have a strong malt flavor, almost like there was a little too low gravity at the end of their mash steep.  Wife didnt enjoy the IPA.  I ordered a London Gentleman (barely wine) just before the check and it never came but I wasn't billed.  

Wife enjoyed her flat bread pizza and 5yr old ate the chicken nuggets (who would have thought).  I had the brisket sandwich and was served pot roast.  You cant make brisket have that texture.  6yrs in Texas which is a brisket BBQ state and more than my fair share or pot roasts at the house, I know those cuts of beef.

Not planning another trip back but if I do itll be for the Nachos.   Saw them dropped at an adjacent table and almost changed my order.  Regrets.

Used to love this place, But its not the same place we fell in love with, now so different. Something has changed. I was really disappointed with my last visit. Extremely slow service, rude employees, cold half cooked ingredients. What happened? Did management change or Ownership? You can tell.
There is no lines anymore. there's always a parking spot now,  All Because nobody likes the new service. They are ruining the good name (Big city burrito). 
Never going back!

Sub par food from a disgusting kitchen at prices that are on par with Chipotle. Literally saw insects flying around the kitchen. I still bought food (nachos) and they were lukewarm at best and on par with nachos you'd get from a movie theater or a gas station. Ambiance was unsettling at best. Seriously nasty dining experience.  Don't understand how this place has such good reviews.

I'm conflicted as to whether or not I liked this place. On one hand, the service was friendly, and the burrito was pretty good with plenty of good options. On the other, the place was all around filthy. The line had cross-contamination written all over it. The dining area was in complete disarray, and felt dirty. What bothered me the most was a dirty glove sitting on the line as he made my burrito. Other negatives included the price, and basic things such as queso and sour cream costing extra even on a veggie-only burrito. In the restaurant industry, presentation is everything and this place unfortunately doesn't seem to get that. I will likely never return.

This place has an amazing burrito, but only if you go when the owner isn’t there. He is so skimpy and rude. I always leave with the smallest burrito and not getting my money’s worth. If i walk in and see him I turn around and leave. They also raised their prices and made their burritos smaller... it’s dissapointing cause they are such yummy burritos.

Tasty burritos. I was eating here around 2004-ish as a teenager and being in an adventurous mood chose the hottest hot sauce on the counter to try. After a few tears from the heat I regretfully chose to wipe my eyes with my fingers. Self-administered pepper spray if you will. After basically taking a bath in the bathroom sink I took the other half of my burrito and left the store with a swollen face and a funny story. lol

Busy place. Worth the crowd! Our family loves the green sauce inside & white sauce outside & extra on the side w/corn tortilla chips! Whether you like sweet pork, steak or chicken w/ black or pinto beans and rice filling you'll get a tasty burrito! I recommend ordering ahead of time to pick up but you can also eat in the restaurant. If you haven't tried it you're missing out.

Cafe Mexicali is a long standing Fort Collins staple. It's the perfect place to go for one of the best smothered burritos you could ever have. It's a quick service place, so it's great if you're wanting a fast, casual lunch or dinner at a reasonable price. The staff has always been extra friendly and helpful for deciding the best flavors to suit any taste. As a visitor there for more than two decades now.l, I can confidently say that Cafe Mexicali is absolutely worth checking out.

They make their tortillas fresh! Food was really good but service was a bit slow. They got our order wrong twice but they were nice about it. I'm pretty sure most of the people who work here are in high school so that could be why. Still super yummy! Get a side of the white cheese sauce OMG! 🤤🤤🤤
Offer guacamole made table side that is yummy. They have a lunch menu that are full size entrees at a lower price. If you like spicy sauce order the next level up from how the menu rates it.

Just ate there yesterday with my grandson. We split a Chicken & a Steak breakfast burritos. They were not only really good, but they were HUGE! The people were very nice & helpful. Even gave me the name of a grocery to look for Chipotle seasoning.

Had China Wok in Marion for years and never disappointed. Tried the one here and the second time I got food poisoning for 3 days from either the chicken lo mien or the crab rangoon or both. Makes me sad but I won’t eat there for a long long time. Just be wary!
Their secret menu (black binder on counter) contains some of the best food items in Carbondale.
Mmmmmmmm egggg rolls!!!
We order from here at least twice a month and it has been our go-to for a couple years now.  Watch the board for new items and specials.   Would not hesitate to recommend.
I have tasted so much better than this. Their spices taste bland.
Called 15 minutes before going to make arrangements to reserve a table for 15 people - no problem... Arrived and we were all served in record time... Excellent server... We will return!
Great little mom and pop diner for breakfast. Decent prices and big portions.
Amazing food and wonderful service. I've only been impressed with this place.
My favorite restaurant!! Absolutely LOVE the green chili, tamales, and chicken fried steak. The staff is top-notch and make you feel at home!!
Great food and service! Reasonable prices.
Th best Mexican food we've found in Colorado, by far! Delicious salsa bar, great service, and outstanding food. The Tarascos sauce itself was enough to bring us back again. New favorite!! ❤️

Highly recommend the "Tarasco sauce" on the chicken enchiladas!  We felt the portions were unusually small and margaritas were too strong. Chips were too thick and hard.  The salsa bar was a great idea but the cups provided to put the salsa in were too small and we found it too hard to dig salsa out with a chip.  Tacos consist of a tiny tortilla with meat.  Not really what we were expecting.

First time here. Service was great. There was a salsa bar which is always a good sign. The food was great and came quickly. But we never felt rushed. Definitely recommend this place to anyone. Only issue is parking but the food was worth the hunt for a parking spot.
Good Mexican food. Excellent margaritas. Our server was super nice. I loved all the salsas at the salsa bar.

Best Mexican Restaurant in old town! The food is amazing, the atmosphere is authentic, the salsa bar is salsa-y, and the margaritas... well they have a two margarita limit, so get a pitcher!! But really I always recommend this place when I talk about Mexican food in old town fort collins! You won't be disappointed and if you are, then it might just be you!

Love the Barrel! The food is delicious and the bartenders are fantastic! Everybody seems like they genuinely enjoy their job and they all work together well! The mural with all the employee's faces on it is so cool and really adds to the family feel this place already has! This is always where we start our night! Their cherry limeade are the bomb!

I used to live in Fort Collins and this is one of two places in town I miss and crave. Their sandwiches are ON POINT. My favorite is the hop sing but everything I've tried has been great. Good ingredients cooked well with nice bread. They have a full bar as well and make mean bloodies. Lastly is the staff- Everyone that works there seems happy and gives wonderful service. Every time I come back to Fort Collins I will be coming here.
The city's best sandwiches reside in this little local bar. Wide variety of beer options as well as some of the best bloodies ever. Plenty of seating and good for kids too.
Absolutely the very best meatball sandwich I've ever had.  I will definitely be back!

Friendly and helpful staff, cozy decor with (finally!) a place putting itself out as a gathering point and puts thought into suppressing the sound so one doesn't have to shout. Sound suppression tiles on the ceiling aside, the food was great and service was quick. The lemon bar was well worth the calories with a tart and none-to-sweet filling and firm base that was chewing and not crumbling. There is patio seating for warm weather, a sports bar - owner appears to love hockey - and a separate kids area decorated with superhero posters instead of sports teams.
Great place for a quick lunch.  Closest thing to subway in this part of the country.  Good choices, especially if looking for low calorie options.  The menus also have the calorie count listed.

UPDATED: We decided to give these guys another shot after chatting with the manager, and are very happy with our second set of subs. We did ask for light mayo and they were perfect.  The lettuce to meat ratio was much better. We will definitely buy from here again. Partially because of the amazing customer service. 

I had been looking forward to trying these subs for a while. Both my husband and I got a sub, and for $6 a piece we were pretty disappointed. Mine had mayonnaise oozing out of it, and his had way too much ranch. We both ended up wiping off condiments from our sandwiches. Also they both had the meat and cheese and then the entire middle was made up of only lettuce.

The bread is subpar- I don't know what it is about this franchise but each time I eat there I am reminded just how much I do not like their Sandwiches.  Great late night option for delivery however  and  have heard, they are a good company to work for.
Little pricy for a sub sandwich but it was loaded with meat! And bread was fresh and seemed homemade.
Good sandwiches. Fair prices

I am always looking for good boba tea hole-in-the-wall spots. Sadly this one was not the best. The boba tea was way too sweet and the dumplings were not good. I think they were microwaved. It was also somewhat expensive for what it was. Sad :(
Delicious food. Always respectful and efficient service. The Boba Tea here is the best offered in Fort Collins.
I love this place! I got my food fast and it is always so delicious! Plus I love the variety of Boba flavors they have! Literally this is my favorite place to get lunch!

I still remember the original "Teriyaki Wok" from the 90's. It's still just as good today, the only thing missing is the big egg rolls they use to sell. The amount of food, plus the quality of the food is excellent, especially for the price. Definitely something that college students can afford, as well as families.
Delicious but Food was cold the first time. However, they gave me a warm dish to replace at no extra charge.

First time here today. I had the watermelon ice cream in a chocolate dipped waffle cone, it was very good and refreshing! My son had a mint chip shake and he loved it. The location is great and right in the middle of town. We grabbed it to go and walked around. Pictures of walruses throughout the shop, that was cute.

Great ice cream. Good amount of toppings. Not a large selection of flavors but they change often and I can always find something good. A bit expensive but worth it. 
 *Please note that the dogs pictured are registered service dogs. They work hard and provide a valuable service to 2 of the people in our group.
Employees were great and friendly and we had quick service. Plenty of flavors to choose from and odd flavors as well. Enjoyed our time there. The ice cream was great!

I absolutely love walrus ice cream. They make the best shakes and they have a lot of unusual flavors but you can't get anywhere else. It's a nice little spot to take the kiddos to get ice cream or you and your girlfriend stop by but if you're in the mood for ice cream I definitely recommend this place it is absolutely awesome. I hope this review helps you decide to go here.
Local and delicious! They have a phenomenal selection of flavors that changes periodically, and the staff has always been great. Definitely a must visit for Fort Collins.

I stopped in on a whim about a month ago and I was so impressed with their gyros that I have been back every week since. Amazing food, amazing service and I love the mom and pop atmosphere. Definitely refreshing and I highly recommend it to anyone else with a craving for delicious food!

That night we were there is wasn't anything exceptional. The service was normal, the atmosphere was dim and dark but rocking the through back jams, the food I'd saw was above par with other Mediterranean restaurants in town. We went during the dinner hours and only 2 other people were dinning in. During the time we were there a few parties order for carry out and I think they knew what was going on. Good food but I wouldn't recommend eat in.
I've been coming here for many, many years. BEST food in town. Owners are welcoming...like family. LOVE this place! Highly recommend!!!!
Good scene for tasty mediterranean food. Normally I would have posted a pic but food looked so good I couldn't stop. Prices are decent.

Great music and comedy nights and the most amazing gyros and gyro salads!  Unbelievable baklava, too! Really creative smoothies, and with a kick off you're in a mood for a saucy incentive libation. The staff and owners always friendly.  Loved this place for 20 years.  💖

Amazing prime rib. Hands down best I've ever had in my life. Service was outstanding, spilled some sauce and had some new sauce in less than a minute. The wait is not so bad with the text alerts for when your table is ready, it let's you explore downtown for awhile while you wait. This place is going to be my birthday spot for life probably.

Good food, great service. Nice, relaxing atmosphere.  I love Austin's.  Try the tasty Beer Battered Walleye, hearty n amazing Chicken Chili, great bacon cheeseburgers, fall off the bone ribs, and don't forget Happy Hour for cheaper food and drinks! Different menus for lunch, happy hour, dinner.... but all are similar.

Nice appetizer, specially shrimps are great. I had meatloaf as the main courses, it was burnt a little but still yummy. Desserts are all good specially the cheesecake. We also ordered the steak, chicken,  and burger which were all good.

Great food and friendly service. I had the porterhouse and the artichoke dip. The drinks were reasonable and well made. Great atmosphere and convenient location in fort Collins. I would go here again for sure.
Right on the probably the busiest corner. So it's great for people watching. Food is always good and service is friendly.

Now this is some dang good pizza! First had it years ago in Idaho Springs and it's as good as i remember it. The mountain pie is loaded with toppings and cheese. Delicious! Be warned, it's very filling! After 2 slices I'm stuffed.... But still want more!

Great corner location!! We were in the area to see a show. One of the few places that weren't packed for the night. Got a great booth facing the street. Great looking decor, modern design. Family ordered a mountain pie and a cauliflower crust pizza. Both were outstanding. We washed both down with a couple of microbrews. Great atmosphere, great service, great pizza!

Nice little pizza joint! The happy hour specials are great, pizza is delicious, and the people are friendly and fabulous. I ordered a calzone, which was absolutely amazing. It was enough for a meal and left overs for the following day. A very nice place, though a bit pricey for pizza.
Great atmosphere, beautiful interior with great windows. Fast and friendly helpful service. Attended family night with a free kids entree and got a balloon butterfly friend to go home with ❤️

Our first visit was amazing. This place has a really unique take on pizza. And the staff was great. That was at least a year or year-and-a-half ago.

Our last visit, which was probably in the summer of 2018, wasn't too great. The pizza was fine. But there were flies all over the place, and we had to constantly keep swatting to keep them away from our food.
Cozy breakfast restaurant with tasty food and hot coffee.. Haven't been disappointed the 4 or 5 times I've been there. Standard breakfast fair and healthy options, too.

Lovely family friendly restaurant. Visited for breakfast. Prices are reasonable and portions are more than sufficient. Enjoyed the Nova Scotia crepes, stuffed with smoked salmon and scrambled eggs.  The home fries were tasty and you have a choice  of different sauces on your table that range form mild to hot spicy.  Their orange cranberry jam is delicious on bread.

Friendly staff and good food. I usually get half orders and coffee when I'm here for brunch, which is more than enough food for me. It's definitely worth a visit if you're in the area and want a good brunch!
Ok place for basic breakfast. Fast friendly service. I had the smoked salmon Benedict. It was good but I've had better in fort Collins.

It was a lovely experience. The food was succulent, palatable, and clean and the atmosphere was peaceful. I got the salmon scrambler and a latte with caramel flavor and  loved them both. Neither were heavy or greasy and the smoked salmon was true to its flavor and freshness. Our gentleman server was very friendly and attentive as well. My significant other and I loved this place.
Best restaurant around. My wife and I are moving out of Fort Collins and are super bummed we can't come here anymore! Always order the specials they never disappoint!

A great little restaurant and bar in South FC, with an upscale intimate feel. Some of their dishes are a little pricey, but they are wonderfully made. The large pizza is a great deal. We had the white pizza last time. We calculated that the large is about two and a third times as large as the smaller size. It can get busy because there are limited tables. The service is great.

Domenic's is still one of my favorite eateries in Fort Collins: lunch or dinner, wine or hand-crafted cocktails -- always very good. Service is consistently welcoming and friendly, and this remains true across the related trio of Domenic's, Vincent and Otto Pint (the beer-centric choice). I'm a fan.
Been here several times, the food is fantastic.  I ordered the Prawns last week and it was excellent.

I don’t leave reviews, but this one needs to be done. We arrived at 5:30 on a Monday night, party of four. We were seated and received drinks and an appetizer quickly, even got a second drink order in before happy hour was up, and had our dinner orders in by 5:45. Then we waited. One of us ordered a couple of appetizers as a meal, so the first of those made it out after a while, and a plate that no one ordered, Then we waited some more. And more. Several tables that were seated after us had already received their checks. Our waitress explained that the kitchen had mixed some things up and our food was next, and it shouldn’t be more than another 5 maybe 6 minutes, and they would even throw in a free dessert. We even got a refill of waters. At this point it was an hour in. And we waited. The second appetizer came out, along with a salad or something that no one ordered. More people who got there after us were leaving. Our drinks were empty. A guy was busy rearranging tables next to us, and we tried to find out what was going on, and he obviously wanted nothing to do with our situation. I guess we were inconveniencing him. Just before 7pm we decided to leave. Hopefully the cash we left helped cover our drinks and appetizers, but there was no end in sight to this nightmare. We had to get out.
Very nice fish & chips the fact you can choose the size of fish is really good small, medium to large.
Good fish chips and all the other goodies you get in a good "Chippie"  and eat in as well
Fish and Chips,nicest I've had in a long time.
Superb food. One of our group (84years old) claimed your "batter to be the best she had ever had!" Great view from upstairs, welcoming staff and would recommend to all.

My family have been coming to this fish shop for years but today will definitely be the last time. My nephew was eating chips and used extra ketchup so a member of staff began shouting at him and became very hostile. Nobody should ever shout at someone else’s child in any manner. Absolutely disgusted by this, my sister got up to leave and doing so they threatened to ban us. Absolutely disgusting how they think they can treat customers like this. Definitely will not be coming back and won’t be recommending to anyone. Definitely need to grow up and be more professional, what happened to the customer is always right?

Went yesterday with my 18 year old daughter. Online It said it was family friendly, and it was for the most part. Of course it was only 3:00 PM in the afternoon. I would expect later in the day / evening this place to turn into full on upscale biker bar. Food was good. My daughter said it was the best burger she had eaten in months. Service was also good, but it was mostly empty.
Best place to be. Not just a biker bar, it's a place for everyone!  Great food, awesome atmosphere. Service is the best, live music nites are even better!  I always feel like I belong!

Came by on a Saturday afternoon and really enjoyed the experience. The staff was incredibly friendly and polite, the food was perfectly seasoned and cooked (absolutely delicious), and the atmosphere was pleasant and modern. I don't make the trek from Denver to Ft. Collins often but this place is a good reason to do so.

Happy hour go-to spot for drinks. Fifty cents off beers and dollar off liquors during happy hour. Afternoon-6pm. Beer is by the bottle only. During happy hour I can get a PBR and a shot of fireball for $4.5. Wow! Food is pub grub style, a little of everything. My favs are the wings and onion rings. Bike nights, Wednesdays during summer months, are pretty wild and usually have a decent live music group.
GREAT FOOD!! GREAT ATMOSPHERE!! GREAT WAITSTAFF!!! We always enjoy Bike Night on Wednesdays thru the summer....Looking forward to going back!!

Was just ok. Was disappointed they didnt even bother to put out any white rice for the lunch buffet and the fried rice was well, overfried. The other items were just barely, meh. For 20 bucks for 2 people, it should have been a lot better. Seemed sloppy.

reviews.author_name: A day in the life of the thurstons thurston
reviews.text: I think its the best Chinese ive ever had joy wah has nothing on this place.
Wonderful food if you get there the beginning of the lunch or dinner hour. Sorry, no more Sunday buffet. Very pleasant staff and dining
Quick service, friendly staff. Menu has good variety and prices are fair.
Slow service, mediocre food. Nice view.

My favorite places to eat breakfast. I bring friends, family, and anyone visiting from out of town. You will impress anyone you bring to this restaurant. The food is amazing! The service has always been good. If you haven’t been, you’re missing a real treat.

I love this place. Could eat here every day. It is so good and the best breakfast in my opinion.
I get the chef's special so I do not have to pick from the menu. Because there are just too many good choices. I never leave disappointed, but you must get there early. The chef's special does run out regularly. Enjoy
Love love loved this place! Went with co workers, can't wait to come back with my husband! Great food and service!
Fantastic Cajun food, esp. breakfast! I just wish they had a second location on Harmony. The lines out the door are unreal, a second location for the south end would be a win/win for everyone!

One of the best places for breakfast/brunch in Front Collins. There is often a wait but it moves quickly and is worth the time. Specials have always been great and having apple butter for biscuits makes me happy every visit. Prices are more than fair with large portions and wonderful service. Highly recommended.

Went in on a Sunday for prime rib. We were told they sold it all on Saturday! We just turned around and left. If you are supposed to be known for prime rib and have it on the menu, it might be a good idea to have some to serve. UPDATE: We decided to give it another try. We went early on a weekday for my birthday. It was a lot better! It was cold outside and we got a booth next to the fireplace...very cozy. I got the prime rib, loaded baked potato, and a Caesar salad. Also got a good Cab. for our wine. All were excellent and the service was super. Great menu selections. We will be back.

The Moot House offers a limited selection of exceptional cuisine.  Moot House dining is delightful for the casual dining experience.  The menu offers a selection from seafood, beef, pork, chicken and a couple of speciality dishes, as well as sides, salads, and lunch menus.

The senior staff at Moot House deliver a pleasant family experience.  Terry, Johnny, Jacob are three of the stable staff members who deliver an exceptional experience.  The selection of local and non-local beverages round out an experience worth entertaining on a regular schedule.

The Moot House may benefit from more than one or two choices in beef, seafood and chicken.  Regardless of the limited menu, the food is always exceptional.

I have seen God this day.
I'm not much of a breakfast person, but I like biscuits and gravy. After today, I have to say that I LOVE biscuits and gravy. And hashbrowns that remind me of Midwestern funeral potatoes, and scrambled eggs that remind me of Sunday morning breakfasts from home.
The warm drinks are beautiful and so so tasty. I want to come here every brunch for the rest of my life.

I went as a Christmas meal with my boss and coworkers. They gave us a separate room that had doors so we didn't have to worry about noise.
The food was good, the creme brulee was delicious, and everyone enjoyed the service, the drinks, and the food equally.
I would go back and I recommend it highly to everyone.

The food is always wonderful and the service is terrific! All the servers are friendly and humorous and management takes a personal interest in each guest having a quality experience. I've had a great time every time I've gone.

I just had my last visit here before moving out of town and I'm distraught. I love the atmosphere and the staff here. The sushi is as good as anywhere in town, but it's peaceful and unhurried and you can have a nice meal with friends where you can actually engage with them not the sound system or the chaos in the restaurant. A great restaurant. I'll sorely miss it.

Went again the other night desperately craving curry but also extra hungry. Got the shrimp curry with a sushi i forget but everything was great and has that quality of making your belly feel like it's at home. Gf loves their vegetable ramen and could barely get half way through it's so filling. The price is higher than most local shops by about $2, BUT you get so much food and variety all of it being a notch better than most sit down places.

We went there tonight with my family. The waitress took forever to even get our drink orders.She never checked on us to refill drinks or checked on us to see how the food was. The food took a long time to get to the table. It was good food but not worth waiting an hour to get after sitting at the table. We've gone here for lunch maybe a dozen times over the last 7 or 8 years and always enjoyed it...not tonight.

I really liked this place. The food was very good, and I think what I most appreciated was the seating. They had a neat hybrid option where you could sit more traditionally on a platform, with the table very low, but the table had a depressed pit under it that you could put your feet in so you were seated in an American style. It got a bit more expensive than I had anticipated or wanted, but overall was a good experience.

My favorite sushi place in Fort Collins. The owners are friendly, staff is helpful, and their food is amazing! My kids love their food and they always remember us. I can't tell you how much I love their sesame chicken! Amazing!

Such an eclectic bunch of shops. I've done Halloween there with my child. Very crowded for Halloween, but beautifully organized for such a large crowd. Love the variety of shops and food. Love day dates where we share an item off the menu of many different places around there.
Great spot to meet up and a small kids play area makes it nice! There's always something going on here and it makes a for a good central location for exploring old town.
Fun! Concerts and scheduals on line. Many culinary and desert choices for all time of the day. Many options in Old Town. Beer any one?
Nice, downtown shopping area. Very dog-friendly. Several restaurants to choose from. Lots of fun shops. Bike rentals. Cheap parking. All around it's a great place to shop.

One of the best place in Fort Collins..
Whenever I'm tired and dont wanna go far in weekends... this is my place.
Good restaurants, bars, live music, water fountains, ice cream centers, sculptures, lights what else you need.
Very safe for everyone so no complains and definitely recommends to others.

Everything was great. Ordered take-out and they had food packaged in large box for easy carrying. Was missing straws for drinks, and didn't get any basil with Pho, though it is listed as accompaniment for each bowl. Website needs some work. Will be back!

The pho with rare steak was very good, and the large size took a little dedication to finish. Well with it for it's price point. The waitress was very quick and attentive, and the place was kept tidy. It's a little boring as far as decor goes, and I almost gave it 4 starts because of that. Check it out!
Good food at a good price. Quite a bit of seating available and the wait staff were pleasant.

I wish I could give more stars and say it was delicious, but I got a takeout Pho  order and they forget my basil and sauces, and by the time I called to ask if I could come grab some, they were closed. Overall though, it tasted ok and they do give a pretty good portion for the price.
Been going to Pho Duy for about 5 years now and i honestly feel like it's the best in town! :)

Delicious and healthy lunch. I loved it, full of veges and chicken in a rich curry, coconut milk sauce. Fabulous cinnamon iced tea. Gracious and friendly service. Fun atmosphere. Will be back again and again!

In a city with abundant good eating places, the Rainbow remains our hands down first choice year after year. Delicious choices for both vegetarians and meat eaters. Breakfast and lunch only and both menus sport excellent choices. Great friendly service, warm cozy brick building with charming interior (formerly a bank with the vault still visible).One of the best if not THE best patio in town. Love love love it.

I was told this was a  vegetarian spot, so wasn't stoked at first. Then I found out they are more than willing to add bacon to anything. Everything I had was incredible! I tried everyone else's food, and my Benedict was incredible! Their pumpkin something pancakes were to die for and made great French toast sticks the next morning. Can't wait to try more of their food!

I’ve loved this place for a long time and have been many many times. Recently however, I’ve taken a break since there is a lot of inconsistency with their food quality and playing, though service is almost always great! This is the reason for 4 stars instead of 5. 

I really want this to be my favorite breakfast restaurant in Fort Collins, perhaps if they can improve consistency this will happen. Either way, I highly recommend you give it a try if you haven’t!

This locally owned restaurant is what Fort Collins is all about! Amazing food. Great people. Excellent service. The outside patio is gorgeous-surrounded by trees and little vegetable gardens. I love it!

Probably the absolute best margarita I've ever had! Unlike most Margaritas that are cloudy because of the lime juice these are crystal clear with a yellow hue. These Margaritas are not for the faint apart I didn't personally ask but those who are with me stated there is a 3 Margarita limit per person, I personally had to I was feeling pretty good luckily I was not behind the wheel. As for the food I can only speak for my steak burrito it was average at best, little to no Mexican flavoring whatsoever. 13 of us gathered in the bar and had great bar service and our waiter was fantastic as well.

Great Mexican food with a twist. Usually busy with a 15-30 minute wait during lunch and dinner and more so on the weekends. Constantly updated menus keeps the place fresh. Of course their margaritas are too notch!

We have passed this restaurant many times while downtown, always busy there, and decided to eat there for Valentine's. It is was outstanding. We made reservations on the website at 2:00 for 4:00 dinner. They had it and seated us immediately. By 5:00, they were very busy. Ordered the house margarita and the agave coin margarita. Very tart and tasty. Complimentary chips and salsa were also good. I ordered the steak fajitas and the wife ordered the crab and shrimp enchiladas. The fajita steak was marinaded with a really flavorful result. The ingredients for assembling the fajitas were fresh and well laid out for ease and convenience. My wife, a seafood lover type, loved her enchiladas. Of course, my big bugaboo is the black beans instead of re-fried pinto beans. Some people like them, and I guess they are OK. But they are always a bit more slimy and veggy tasting than re-fried pintos. But these were good. The waitress was very friendly and accommodating. Lots of good atmosphere here as well. I recommend this eatery for southwest food and service.

We have been going here for about 20 years. The food and margs are very good......I gave three stars instead of 5 because of the poor customer service...not from the wait staff but from the management. They have a employee meeting prior to opening on Saturday morning at 11am. They usually run late, which means they don't open the front door till the meeting is done5-10 minutes later, when there is line forming and people ticked off, especially when the weather is bad. Management is giving a bad example of "service" to their employees. While they are talking about giving good service, the people who keep them open are waiting for you to open when you say you will.

This place is known for their margaritas, rightfully so but they have lots of tasty food. My favorite is the grilled steak nachos. Very popular so if you want to go there Friday or Saturday, reservations are recommended.

The Chilli House offers a wide selection of traditional American-Chinese, Thai cuisine for the local community.  Chili House offers perhaps the best option for Chinese, Thai and sushi foods within the city of Fort Collins.  

Comparatively reviewing Chili House with several restaurants offering similar cuisine across Colorado and other major metropolitan communities, Chili House fails to meet the authenticity and quality of traditional Chinese, Thai food and sushi dishes.

Chili House fails to offer true, authentic, high quality Chinese and Thai foods with the taste, substantive elements, and authenticity.  Taste, flavor, quality are all factors subject to improvement for true Chinese, Thai cuisine.  Comparatively reviewing Chili House, the cost of dining at Chili House is in excess of the best Chinese, Thai restaurants across Colorado and many other states.

Less positive reviews offer businesses an opportunity to improve where they may fall short in their products and services.  Chili House could improve their authenticity while aligning their prices with the lower cost at better Chinese, Thai restaurants.

Good quantity of pretty good food for a cheap price.  Edit: Ive went many times with no problem. Today though, ordered, waited 45 minutes while everyone who came in after us got their soup and meals before we got any soup.  We had a party of 3, all the parties that came in after had more people. 
No one came and checked in with us.

The Chili House is a great restaurant for the family or for date. The waiters make excellent recommendations. The food is fresh and flavorful. The portion sizes are generous. The environment is cozy. I highly recommend.

Food is excellent. 3 star rating is for the awful service. Showed up and a man took me too my table. I was meeting 3 other people but he didn't care to ask. He kept rushing me and finally after being told two times I had other guests he stopped rushing me. Chili House, there is a massive difference between being attentive and rushing your guests out. Definitely won't be going back. There's better Asian food at Asian Grill Express or Wok and Roll. And they welcome all guests.

Our goto for Oriental food. Always really good and they deliver. The price is amazing compared to other places in town. The dine in is great, eclectic and clean. Generally a busy place which is a good thing.

Love the Barrel! The food is delicious and the bartenders are fantastic! Everybody seems like they genuinely enjoy their job and they all work together well! The mural with all the employee's faces on it is so cool and really adds to the family feel this place already has! This is always where we start our night! Their cherry limeade are the bomb!

I used to live in Fort Collins and this is one of two places in town I miss and crave. Their sandwiches are ON POINT. My favorite is the hop sing but everything I've tried has been great. Good ingredients cooked well with nice bread. They have a full bar as well and make mean bloodies. Lastly is the staff- Everyone that works there seems happy and gives wonderful service. Every time I come back to Fort Collins I will be coming here.
The city's best sandwiches reside in this little local bar. Wide variety of beer options as well as some of the best bloodies ever. Plenty of seating and good for kids too.
Absolutely the very best meatball sandwich I've ever had.  I will definitely be back!

Friendly and helpful staff, cozy decor with (finally!) a place putting itself out as a gathering point and puts thought into suppressing the sound so one doesn't have to shout. Sound suppression tiles on the ceiling aside, the food was great and service was quick. The lemon bar was well worth the calories with a tart and none-to-sweet filling and firm base that was chewing and not crumbling. There is patio seating for warm weather, a sports bar - owner appears to love hockey - and a separate kids area decorated with superhero posters instead of sports teams.
Excellent Service

We have been eating here for almost 20 years and are so sad they are closing.  We went tonight for dinner and it was crazy busy!  Everyone trying to get a last meal before the restaurant is gone.  
  Always so good.  Thank you for all the wonderful memories and food!
Probably the best Thai food I've ever had. A real shame that they're closing. However, I'm very excited about being able to buy their cook book when it comes out.
Excellent food! Many gluten free options. The service is outstanding and it is very clean. Great atmosphere.  I highly recommend this restaurant!

When I first moved here, I tried several Thai restaurants and was disappointed each time...until I found Sri Thai! Each dish I have tried has been unique and delicious...and when I'm sick nothing but Sri Thai Tom Yum soup will do. Their mango sticky rice is legendary, I appreciate that they only serve it when the mangos are in season!
Absolutely delicious food! I LOVE the Panang Curry and usually get that. I decided to try a stir fry at my most recent trip and it was very, very tasty. Yum!!

We just got a to go order for our daughters birthday meal, we picked up 2 dragon sushi rolls. Kinda pricey,  cost about 37 dollars for 2. The taste was pretty good, some of the fish seemed a bit chewy,  dont think they used the highest quality for the price. There was cucumber in the sushi roll, again this was different from what we were used to, but still good.  Took 40 minutes to get the order, but it was a Saturday night... uniforms of the staff, seemed, underclass for a higher priced sushi bar. I think people go to this because it is trendy, not a classy type place. There is also a bar that you can sit at as well. We have visited sushi bars in California and Ohio. So if I was to compare. I would rate food and atmosphere at about a 6.5, but if I was from the younger crowd and not real knowledgeable about great tasting sushi, possibly an 8.

Best sushi in town!!  High quality, tasty sushi rolls. Bento box is also a fantastic option for someone who doesn't care for raw fish. My kids love them!!  Thank you Connor for your wonderful customer service!  Will definitely be back!

Our favorite sushi spot in northern Colorado! This place has great lunch specials, quality fish that's always fresh and delicious, and great service with knowledgeable staff. The presentation if the dishes is always nice and the restaurant is always clean. I highly recommend their signature rolls and sashimi.

It was so busy last night, Friday, we had to sit as a family of four with two teenagers at the Sushi bar.  Chance took care of us, and it was the best experience out of many years of dining at Suehiro.  He was awesome,  helpful, and funny.  What a treat.  Thank you!  We love this place, and now you have given us another reason to rant about Suehiro.

Really good food, but never consistently. We did the chef creation and I could hear the cook complaining about having to create something. Usually it's our favorite because they have fun and create something amazing. Bartender has no clue how to make an old fashioned, hint it does not have maraschino cherries in it. Hopefully next time things go better.

I couldn’t tell you how the food is because upon arriving we were confused about where the host wanted to seat us. We explained it was our First time in and decided to go with the BBQ table. After 10 minutes of trying to figure out their menu which was hard to understand no one had even come to take our drink order much less answer any of our first timer questions. There were 3 occupied tables and I saw 4 servers and a host. As we left the host said “have a good night”. Must have forgotten he just seated us.

It is hard to give an unbiased review when you are doing the cooking. The servers appeared frequently and were friendly. The meat came out promptly, and appeared very cleanly cut and fresh. I ordered the family #4 with beef short ribs and chicken, that we grilled to perfection. The side of sushi was very good. All the side dishes were better than the last time, I'm guessing they're trying new things. Dinner finished with the fried banana ice cream, fantastic.

My daughter has fully embraced K-Pop and the Korean culture. I surprised them with dinner at Suh Sushi. The food was delicious. There is choice of preparing the meat at your table or having the chef prepare it.  We prepared at our table. The experience was wonderful. The food was delicious. The quantity of meat for a family of four was slight small. The side dishes were enough to quince your appetite. Encourage you to try it.

Fantastic food, I have yet to try anything that was not delicious! A great atmosphere for a long meal, and Korean BBQ is quite the experience. Dinner prices are on par with any other nice restaurant but are well worth it, but the lunch deals are great.

Food was good, service was very slow. Went at off hours, greeted promptly and sat next to the people who were behind us in line. 30 minutes later the people who came in behind us had their food and our server had yet to bring us water. 

This appears to be dependent on random luck, so we will try again soon.

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.
The food was really good with organic ingredients and fresh veggies. The service was good too!
Calamari tough and chewy, spring mix laced with pieces that have turned, garlic shrimp over salted and shrimp mushy. Cucumber salad was ok.
Server was very nice but the food was certainly overpriced for its quality.. Pretty salty and also $10 for an appetizer of spring rolls seemed pretty outrageous..

Went here for a holiday party. The staff was great, lots of patience and super kind. The only thing that I liked from their food though was the steak, everything else tasted like they lost either spice rack.. totally bland..

Tiger rolls. This is the only place that has them anywhere and they are heavenly. Awesome outdoor seating overlooking the creek. Prices are higher than they should be but they cater to the tourist clientele/one time dinner guest. Very busy venue. Reservations recommended.

Overall, we had a great dining experience.  Service was quick and friendly.  Pizza was hot and good.  I wish they had mixed all the toppings all over the pizza instead of just putting one topping per three pieces, not a fan of that.  Our crust was burnt on the bottom as well.  Atmosphere was amazing, however.

I wish that yelp gave more then just 5 stars because this place deserves at least a solid 10! I can honestly say that they have amazing customer service, and the owners make you feel at home. Their family-friendly attitude is what a lot of modern day restaurants are lacking. And not to mention the food is INCREDIBLE, I not only crave it all the time now but am never let down again every time I go there. I can’t wait to go back, till the next time!! And you can tell that they serve fresh homemade ingredients! THIS PLACE IS A MUST GO!! YOU WILL NOT BE DISAPPOINTED!! And p.s. I love the new set up! It doesn’t change the customer service or food at all!!
This place is perfect for family or friend gatherings! Delicious pizza, drinks and an incredible outdoor patio! I love the prices and  ease if ordering as well!

Newly reopened and was very busy, early evening. We ordered 2 pizzas by phone for pick up and they were ready within 20/25 minutes. Had ordered pizza before it was closed for "renovation," and the pizzas were delicious. The restaurant looked very much the same, but can't say that for the pizza, unfortunately. Both pizzas we're ordered with tomato sauce. Blah. Dry. It's as if a tomato were passed over the pizzas; tomato sauce was a rare find.   Be that as it may, we're willing to give it a pass, considering how busy it was and that they only recently reopened. We'll definitely be back - - - a second chance is in order under the circumstances, and we sincerely hope our experience was only an aberration and the restaurant is successful.
Great Restaurant!  The staff is GREAT!  The food was wonderful and my margarita was on point! Very family friendly!  We have found our go to spot!!

High class atmosphere. Food is incredible. This is definitely my favorite place downtown to chill and and enjoy good conversation. Live local music is a real treat. The dirty blue goose martini is the best I've had anywhere. Good for flying solo or with a group!

Our company brings in the new year at a top shelf restaurant in Fort Collins every year and we thought we would try something new this year.  We could not have been more pleased.  Every bottle of wine and every dish was perfect.  We are not snobs but we all know how to cook and we know when something is cooked with care.  These chefs blew our minds.  Everyone was elated with their food and the service was top notch.  Ambiance was great.  We could not be happier and we will come to this restaurant again in our professional and private lives.  A++++++

Great service, food, and awesome college atmosphere. Did you know Sonny Lubick won a national championship with Miami? He even has the championship ring showcased in the main dining room to prove it. Awesome spot. I'll definitely be going back. Oh, and try the venison - I don't know what to compare it to but it is the sushi grade flavor and quality of red meat!! Delicious.

The food is amazing, the staff is inviting and personable, and the environment is comfortable and relaxing. I have been here twice now for date night and the experience is wonderful, we will definitely be back and will recommend to family and friends.
This is the best steak in Fort Collins. I usually get the bacon wrapped filet and the beef tartare. The drink specials are always unique and delicious, and it has a pretty decent whiskey list.
